CALIFORNIA RIDGE WIND ENERGY LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
California Ridge Wind Energy LLC ("California Ridge") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the California Ridge generating facility ("California Ridge Facility").
California Ridge is a 227 MW wind turbine generating facility located in Vermillion and Champaign, Illinois. The California Ridge Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Ameren Illinois Company and under the operational control of the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ("MISO").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth California Ridge's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the California Ridge Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
California Ridge's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to California Ridge shall be subject to Schedule 2 of MISO's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $668,500.00. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $55,708.33.
